Computer Networking = Terminal(단말기) + Network Machine
Terminal = Client + Server
LAN = Local Area Network

OSI(Open System Interconnection reference) : 7 Layers 
frame = header + payload
WAN(Wide Area Network) = LAN x N
IP(Internet Protocol)

Layer 1 : Hardware
Layer 2 : frame(data)
Layer 3 : packet(data)


stream is just data stream
file transfer EOF(Header or Delimiter)
Header : Header + Data
Delimiter : Data + Delimiter

Unlike streams, messages can distinguishing beginning point and the end of data 
Message example : 
0 ~ 1 MessageType_FireBullet
2 ~ 13 Position(x,y,z)
14 ~ 25 Direction(x,y,z)
26 ~ 27 Bullet Type

Fragmentation(단편화) 

Ports in Process in Terminal

DNS Server : host name transfer IP address

Layer 1 Hareware : Basically Data is changed into an electric signal or electromagnetic wave signal of a certain 
amplitude or frequency in the process of going out to a wired or wireless line and is emitted.

Latency(전송 지연 시간)

UDP (User Datagram Protocol)
